items.title: Elevated Blood Glucose
items.description: High glucose levels suggest poor glucose control or a pre-diabetic condition.

items.title: High LDL Cholesterol
items.description: Excessive Low-Density Lipoprotein cholesterol often suggests an unhealthy diet or possible heart disease.

items.title: Low Hemoglobin
items.description: Hemoglobin carries oxygen in the blood, and low levels might be indicative of anemia or another blood disorder.

items.title: Heart Health
items.description: Balanced diet, exercise, and regular check-ups maintain effective blood pumping.

items.title: Liver Health
items.description: Low-fat diet, exercise, and moderate alcohol use help in detoxification and blood clotting.

items.title: Kidney Health
items.description: Balanced diet, hydration, and reduced sodium intake support waste filtration and bodily fluid regulation.

items.title: Immune System Health
items.description: Nutritious diet, exercise, sleep, hygiene, and vaccinations aid in boosting immune response and disease prevention.
